Description: PuTTY session manager with tabbed terminals
 Tabber is a modern GTK4/libadwaita application that provides a tabbed
 terminal interface for managing PuTTY/plink SSH, Telnet, Serial, and
 Raw sessions on Ubuntu.
 .
 Features include:
  * Tabbed terminal sessions with browser-like tab management
  * Sidebar with saved connections organized into groups/folders
  * Quick connect bar for fast ad-hoc connections
  * Split panes (horizontal/vertical) within tabs
  * Broadcast input mode to send keystrokes to all sessions
  * Color-coded tabs and session groups
  * Auto-reconnect on disconnection
  * Session logging to files
  * Terminal search (Ctrl+Shift+F)
  * SFTP file transfer dialog
  * Command snippets library
  * PuTTY session import/export compatibility
  * Full keyboard shortcut support
